I.	Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at 555 Northwest Avenue, LLC in Northlake, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This 5-year, updated Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 
	Introduction;
	555 Northwest Avenue, LLC policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
	Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
	Hazard Assessment;
	Prevention Program;
	Five-Year Accident History;
	Emergency Response Plan; 
	Emergency Communications;
	Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
	Planned changes to improve safety; and
	Management Program

II.	555 Northwest Avenue, LLC Policies To Protect Health, Environment and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at 555 Northwest Avenue, LLC; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. 555 Northwest Avenue, LLC is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is 555 Northwest Avenue, LLC policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations. 

